# Database Migrations

## How migrations run

Migrations auto-run via `MigrationService.php` on every API request. But when giving the user the manual MySQL command, ALWAYS use this exact format:

```
mysql -u vpsadmin -p'7bcf619af819e4e274e5cfdfba022274' devc_vps_dash < /var/www/vps-email/backend/migrations/MIGRATION_FILE.sql
```

## Example

For a migration file `120_mood_board_component_instances.sql`:

```
mysql -u vpsadmin -p'7bcf619af819e4e274e5cfdfba022274' devc_vps_dash < /var/www/vps-email/backend/migrations/120_mood_board_component_instances.sql
```

## Credentials

- DB user: `vpsadmin`
- DB pass: `7bcf619af819e4e274e5cfdfba022274`
- DB name: `devc_vps_dash`
- Server path: `/var/www/vps-email/backend/migrations/`

## Rules

- ALWAYS include the password inline with `-p'PASSWORD'` (no space between -p and the password)
- NEVER use `source` command
- NEVER use placeholder paths like `/path/to/`
- ALWAYS provide the full ready-to-paste command with the actual filename
